  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Adjunct HSE / Fire-Fighting Trainer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Deliver HSE and fire-fighting training programs to clients, lead emergency response simulations, and train personnel in the effective use of fire-fighting equipment to enhance safety preparedness and emergency response capabilities.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Deliver comprehensive theoretical and practical HSE and fire-fighting training to clients, ensuring knowledge transfer and skill acquisition</li><li>Lead emergency response simulations to evaluate and improve client readiness for fire and hazardous material incidents</li><li>Train personnel in the correct operation of fire-fighting equipment, including fire extinguishers, hoses, and breathing apparatus, to ensure effective emergency response</li><li>Provide first response training for fire, hazardous materials, and emergency incidents to enhance client safety protocols</li><li>Deliver engaging classroom and field-based training sessions that promote active learning and skill retention</li><li>Demonstrate fire-fighting techniques physically to model correct procedures and ensure trainee competence</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Practical knowledge of fire-fighting equipment and emergency response techniques</li><li>Physical fitness to demonstrate fire-fighting techniques effectively</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Strong presentation and communication skills to engage diverse audiences during training sessions</li><li>Ability to conduct engaging classroom and field-based training to maximize participant learning</li><li>Good report writing and documentation skills to maintain accurate training records and compliance documentation</li></ul>",
